{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandate working a/c and heating systems on all new public transport vehicles",
        "additional_details": "The UK still has:\r\n\u2022 no legal maximum bus cab temperature;\r\n\u2022 no dedicated bus driver heat safety framework;\r\n\u2022 no nationally enforceable cooling standards;\r\n\u2022 no DVSA standards on excessive cab temperatures;\r\n\u2022 and no nationally agreed operational heatwave procedures for the bus industry.\r\n \r\nThings that will need to be considered are:\r\n\u2022 driver cab cooling;\r\n\u2022 occupational heat protection;\r\n\u2022 climate control standards;\r\n\u2022 fatigue management;\r\n\u2022 and heatwave operational procedures.\r\n \r\nLet's make change!\r\n",
        "background": "Heatwaves are becoming increasingly more frequent, so let's get working air conditioning and heating systems made a legal requirement before a new public service vehicle can go in to service.",
